  <span class="word-original hebrew">הַ/זֶּֽה\׃\ \ס</span>
  <span class="word-translit">ha/Zeh</span>
  <span class="word-english">the/ this</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9009</span>
</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here the word “now” is used to draw attention to the important point that follows.
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The eyes being open is a metonym for seeing. Here it represents looking attentively. Alternate translation: [please pay attention to us] or [please look at us]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The ears being attentive is a metonym for listening attentively. Alternate translation: [please listen to the prayer]
    </div><div class="interlinear-verse hebrew-verse"><span class="verse-num">41</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9002">
