  <span class="word-original hebrew">אַל\־</span>
  <span class="word-translit">&#x27;al-</span>
  <span class="word-english">may not</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h408.html">H408</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H7725">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">תָּשֵׁ֖ב</span>
  <span class="word-translit">taShev</span>
  <span class="word-english">you turn away</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h7725.html">H7725</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H6440">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">פְּנֵ֣י</span>
  <span class="word-translit">peNei</span>
  <span class="word-english">the faces of</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h6440.html">H6440</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H4899">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">מְשִׁיחֶ֑י/ךָ</span>
  <span class="word-translit">meshiChei/kha</span>
  <span class="word-english">anointed one/ your</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h4899.html">H4899</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H2142">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">זָכְרָ֕/ה</span>
  <span class="word-translit">zakheRa/h</span>
  <span class="word-english">remember/ !</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h2142.html">H2142</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9005">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">לְ/חַֽסְדֵ֖י</span>
  <span class="word-translit">le/chasDei</span>
  <span class="word-english">to/ the covenant loyalties of</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9005</span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H1732">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">דָּוִ֥יד</span>
  <span class="word-translit">daVid</span>
  <span class="word-english">David</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h1732.html">H1732</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H5650">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">עַבְדֶּֽ/ךָ\׃\ \פ</span>
  <span class="word-translit">&#x27;avDe/kha</span>
  <span class="word-english">servant/ your</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h5650.html">H5650</a></span>
</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Turning the face of someone away represents rejecting him. Alternate translation: [do not reject your anointed one]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> “your anointed one.” Being anointed is a metonym for being chosen by God. King Solomon may have been speaking specifically about himself. If your language does not use the passive form in this way, you can state this in active form or in another way that is natural in your language. Alternate translation: [the one you anointed] or [me, the one you chose to be king] (See also: [[
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The phrase “your acts” can be expressed with the phrase “what you have done.” Alternate translation: [Remember what you have done for David, your servant, because of your covenant loyalty]
    </div>
